label: filter fractionation size
definition: A size quality which inheres in an aquatic environmental material sample by virtue of such bearer being size fractioned via a filtration process.

label: maximum filter fractionation size
definition: A size quality which inheres in an aquatic environmental material sample by virtue of being the maximum particle size obtained when such bearer is subject to a size fractionating filtration process.

label: minimum filter fractionation size
definition: A size quality which inheres in an aquatic environmental material sample by virtue of being the minimum particle size obtained when such bearer is subject to a size fractionating filtration process.

label: NCBI accession number
definition: A specimen identifier assigned by sequencing facility which is assigned by the National Center for Biotechnology Information.

label: SRA accession number
definition: A specimen identifier assigned by sequencing facility which identifies a Sequence Read Archive (SRA) acession number.

label: latitude start
definition: A measurement datum that is the measure of the starting latitude coordinate of a site during a specimen collection process.

label: latitude stop
definition: A measurement datum that is the measure of the latitude coordinate of a site at the end of a specimen collection process.

label: longitude start
definition: A measurement datum that is the measure of the starting longitude coordinate of a site during a specimen collection process.

label: longitude stop
definition: A measurement datum that is the measure of the longitude coordinate of a site at the end of a specimen collection process.

label: sample collection start time
definition: A time measurement datum that is the measure of the start time when the specimens are collected.

label: sample collection end time
definition: A time measurement datum that is the measure of the time when the specimens are finished being collected.

label: sample collection date
definition: A data item that indicates the time when the collection of a specimen occurred.
editors note: In OMIABIS should add to OBI?

label: sample collection date start
definition: A data item that indicates the time when the collection of a specimen began.

label: sample collection date end
definition: A data item that indicates the time when the collection of a specimen ended.
